   <conbody>
      <p class="- topic/p ">You can exclude products or sub-category from a category. Excluding a product from a category provides you with the flexibility to modify the price of a product when you already have the category as part of the beneficiary line. You can add the excluded product or sub-category as a different benefit line with its own benefit price.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">To exclude a product or sub-category from a category,</p>
      <ol class="- topic/ol ">
         <li class="- topic/li ">Navigate to the Qualifications &amp; Benefits tab of your program.</li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">Click Exclude next to the category to exclude the product. The Exclude Products pop-up opens.<fig class="- topic/fig ">
               <image height="250"
                      placement="break"
                      width="568"
                      href="../attachments/102432697/107118622.png"
                      class="- topic/image "/>
            </fig>
         </li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">From the Category, select your product to exclude.</li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">Click Exclude. Selected product moves under the Excluded Products tab.</li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">Click Save.</li>
      </ol>
